Bonaparte, having come up at a gallop, stopped his horse.

â€œWhich is the senior?â€ he asked, on seeing the prisoners.

They named the colonel, Prince RepnÃ­n.

â€œYou are the commander of the Emperor Alexanderâ€™s regiment of Horse
Guards?â€ asked Napoleon.

â€œI commanded a squadron,â€ replied RepnÃ­n.

â€œYour regiment fulfilled its duty honorably,â€ said Napoleon.

â€œThe praise of a great commander is a soldierâ€™s highest reward,â€
said RepnÃ­n.

â€œI bestow it with pleasure,â€ said Napoleon. â€œAnd who is that young
man beside you?â€

Prince RepnÃ­n named Lieutenant SukhtÃ©len.

After looking at him Napoleon smiled.

â€œHeâ€™s very young to come to meddle with us.â€

â€œYouth is no hindrance to courage,â€ muttered SukhtÃ©len in a failing
