CHAPTER IX

BilÃ­bin was now at army headquarters in a diplomatic capacity, and
though he wrote in French and used French jests and French idioms,
he described the whole campaign with a fearless self-censure and
self-derision genuinely Russian. BilÃ­bin wrote that the obligation of
