the hill, they threw up their caps and shouted: â€œVive lâ€™Empereur!â€ and
one after another poured in a ceaseless stream out of the vast forest
that had concealed them and, separating, flowed on and on by the three
bridges to the other side.

â€œNow weâ€™ll go into action. Oh, when he takes it in hand himself, things
get hot... by heaven!... There he is!... Vive lâ€™Empereur! So these
are the steppes of Asia! Itâ€™s a nasty country all the same. Au revoir,
