â€œAh, my God! my God! When one thinks who and whatâ€”what trashâ€”can cause
people misery!â€ he said with a malignity that alarmed Princess Mary.

She understood that when speaking of â€œtrashâ€ he referred not only to
Mademoiselle Bourienne, the cause of her misery, but also to the man who
