At SmolÃ©nsk the armies at last reunited, much as BagratiÃ³n disliked it.

BagratiÃ³n drove up in a carriage to the house occupied by Barclay.
Barclay donned his sash and came out to meet and report to his senior
officer BagratiÃ³n.

Despite his seniority in rank BagratiÃ³n, in this contest of magnanimity,
