CHAPTER XXXVI

Prince Andrewâ€™s regiment was among the reserves which till after one
oâ€™clock were stationed inactive behind SemÃ«novsk, under heavy artillery
fire. Toward two oâ€™clock the regiment, having already lost more than
two hundred men, was moved forward into a trampled oatfield in the gap
