CHAPTER XXVI

Toward four oâ€™clock in the afternoon Muratâ€™s troops were entering
Moscow. In front rode a detachment of WÃ¼rttemberg hussars and behind
them rode the King of Naples himself accompanied by a numerous suite.

About the middle of the ArbÃ¡t Street, near the Church of the Miraculous
Icon of St. Nicholas, Murat halted to await news from the advanced
