PlatÃ³n with one of his round smiles, obviously pleased with his work.

â€œItâ€™s good, quite good, thank you,â€ said the Frenchman, in French, â€œbut
there must be some linen left over.â€

â€œIt will fit better still when it sets to your body,â€ said KaratÃ¡ev,
still admiring his handiwork. â€œYouâ€™ll be nice and comfortable....â€

â€œThanks, thanks, old fellow.... But the bits left over?â€ said the
