Toll wrote a disposition: â€œThe first column will march to so and so,â€
etc. And as usual nothing happened in accord with the disposition.
Prince EugÃ¨ne of WÃ¼rttemberg fired from a hill over the French crowds
that were running past, and demanded reinforcements which did not
