had known him before, and despite his abhorrence of the civil service,
he accepted a post in Moscow in that service, doffed the uniform of
which he was so fond, and moved with his mother and SÃ³nya to a small
house on the SÃ­vtsev VrazhÃ³k.

NatÃ¡sha and Pierre were living in Petersburg at the time and had no
clear idea of Nicholasâ€™ circumstances. Having borrowed money from his
